
Peter Berger (rower)
instance
Peter Berger (born October 16, 1949) is a German rower who competed for West Germany in the 1968 Summer Olympics and in the 1972 Summer Olympics. He was born in Konstanz. In 1968 he was a crew member of the West German boat which finished twelfth in the coxed fours event. Four years later he won the gold medal with the West German boat in the coxed fours competition.
